"/> Is there a credit union in your area that you are eligible to join? Their
terms will likely be MUCH better for a loan and/or a secured credit card.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; I went to some car
&gt; dealers and applied for a car loan. One of them is giving me 12.25%
&gt; interest rate for 5 years.

"/> WAY too much! You need a good, inexpensive used car, and a loan for 2 or 3
years. Otherwise you'll dig a hole that will be hard to get out of!

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; I don't know if I should go for it to help
&gt; establish my credit and refinance it after a year or just use the
&gt; downpayment to get an old car and hope that the secured credit card
&gt; would be approved. But i was thinking that the secured card's amount
&gt; is very small and it looks like a large amount for a car loan on my
&gt; record will be good. Or does it matter at all?

"/> NO!!!

Do NOT saddle yourself with debt in an attempt to establish a credit rating.
Start small, and work your way up.

You don't say what your job or salary range is, but your debt cannot be out
of line with your income.

</POST>



